pageContext.description: Fainted trace of ornament below stop. Cast marks show. Fracture shows some impure composition. Edge has been ground but is much broken. as in companion piece analysed by Prof. Desch.
pageContext.surface: Apple green much blistered by corrosion.
pageContext.associations: One of 4 fragments (hoard) from same place + 1 specimen in B.M.
pageContext.publications: Handbook of the Museum of the Albert Institute. Says 200 yards from Bishopgate in the Park. Windsor Road.
pageContext.collection: Ashmolean Museum, Oxford,Received 1925 in exchange from Hull Municipal Museum.,Purchased from Windsor Museum
